==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Commorancy
<hw>Com"mo*ran*cy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Law)</fld> <def>A dwelling or ordinary residence in a place;
habitation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Commorancy</qex> consists in usually lying there.</q>
<rj><qau>Blackstone.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Am. Law)</fld> <def>Residence temporarily, or for a
short time.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Commorant</ent>⟦br⟧
